{{Infobox ancient site | name = Ōtsukayama Kofun | native_name = 大塚山古墳 | native_name_lang = | image = 会津大塚山古墳.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Ōtsukayama Kofun | map_type = Japan Fukushima Prefecture#Japan | map_alt = Location in Japan | relief = 1 | map_caption = Ōtsukayama Kofun | map_size = 270px | altitude_m = | altitude_ref = 37°30′46″N 139°56′39″E | coordinates = {{coord|37|30|46|N|139|56|39|E|display=inline, title}} | map_dot_label = | location = [[Aizuwakamatsu, Fukushima]], [[Japan]] | region = [[Tohoku region]] | type = kofun | part_of = | length = | width = | area = | volume = | diameter = | circumference = | height = | built = [[Kofun period]] | abandoned = | epochs = | cultures = | discovered = | excavations = | archaeologists = | condition = | ownership = National Historic Site | management = | public_access = Yes | other_designation = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | architectural_styles = | architectural_details = | notes = }} {{nihongo|'''Ōtsukayama Kofun'''|大塚山古墳|Aizu-Ōtsukayama Kofun}} is an early [[Kofun period]] (6th century AD) [[kofun|key-hole shaped tumulus]] located in what is now part of the city of [[Aizuwakamatsu, Fukushima]] in the southern [[Tohoku region]] of [[Japan]]. The site was designated a [[Monuments of Japan|National Historic Site of Japan]] in 1972.<ref name="Bunka">{{cite web |url= http://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/209660 |title=大塚山古墳|trans-title= Ōtsukayama Kofun|language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=}}</ref> It is the second largest kofun in Fukushima Prefecture after the [[Kamegamori-Chinjumori Kofun|Kamegamori kofun]] and the fourth largest in the Tohoku region. The [[grave goods]] recovered from the ''kofun'' were collectively designated a National [[Important Cultural Property of Japan]] in 1977.<ref name="Bunka2">{{cite web |url= http://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/187522 |title=会津大塚山古墳出土品|trans-title= Aizu-Ōtsukayama Kofun Artifacts|language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=}}</ref>
==Overview== [[File:会津大塚山古墳南棺出土 三角縁唐草文帯三神二獣鏡.JPG|right|thumb|Bronze Mirror recovered from the Ōtsukayama ''kofun'', a National ICP]] The Ōtsukayama ''kofun'' is located in the eastern portion of Aizu Basin, near the center of Aizuwakamatsu. It has a total length of 114 meters, with a rectangular portion length of 54 meters, and a rear circle diameter of 70 meters with a height of 10 meters. The domed portion was built in three tiers and the rectangular portion in two tiers, and it dates from the early Kofun period (the second half of the 4th century). The tomb was excavated in 1988, and a large number of artifacts were recovered from the [[burial chamber], which contained two graves. The artifacts in the southern sarcophagus included a [[bronze mirror]], [[magatama]], tubular beads, fragments of swords, armor and whetstones, for a total of 279 items. The northern sarcophagus included [[Spindle (textiles)|spindles]], cylindrical beads and knives, for a total of 95 items.Many of these items are on display at the [[Fukushima Museum]] in Aizuwakamatsu.
==See also== *[[List of Historic Sites of Japan (Fukushima)]]
